.SH "NAME"
cz \- conventional commit message builder
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.sp
\fBcz\fP [\fB\-c\fP \fIFILE\fP] [\fISUBCOMMAND\fP]
.sp
\fBcz\fP \fBcreate\fP [\fB\-s\fP]
.br
\fBcz\fP \fBlint\fP [\fB\-q\fP]
.br
\fBcz\fP \fBparse\fP
.br
\fBcz\fP \fBinit\fP [\fB\-f\fP]
.br
\fBcz\fP \fBhook\fP [\fBinstall\fP | \fBuninstall\fP | \fBstatus\fP]
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.sp
\fBcz\fP is an interactive tool for creating commit messages that follow the
Conventional Commits specification. It can also lint existing messages or
display the resolved configuration.
.sp
When invoked without a subcommand, \fBcz\fP defaults to \fBcreate\fP mode if run
in a terminal, or \fBlint\fP mode if receiving input on standard input.
.SH "SUBCOMMANDS"
.sp
\fBcreate\fP [\fB\-s\fP]
.RS 4
Compose a commit message interactively using \fBgum\fP(1). Prompts for type,
scope, breaking change indicator, description, body, and footer. Output
is written to standard output. Default when run interactively.
Requires \fBgum\fP to be installed.
.sp
\fB\-s\fP, \fB\-\-strict\-scopes\fP
.RS 4
Only allow scopes defined in configuration, disabling custom input.
By default, configured scopes are shown as suggestions with an option
to enter a custom scope.
.RE
.RE
.sp
\fBlint\fP [\fB\-q\fP]
.RS 4
Validate a commit message against the Conventional Commits rules and the
\fB.gitcommitizen\fP(5) configuration. Reads from standard input. Prints
diagnostic messages explaining any errors. Exits non\-zero if validation
fails.
.sp
\fB\-q\fP, \fB\-\-quiet\fP
.RS 4
Suppress output. Only set the exit status.
.RE
.RE
.sp
\fBparse\fP
.RS 4
Display configuration with all values expanded. Useful for debugging.
.RE
.sp
\fBinit\fP [\fB\-f\fP]
.RS 4
Generate a starter \fB.gitcommitizen\fP file in the current directory.
.sp
\fB\-f\fP, \fB\-\-force\fP
.RS 4
Overwrite an existing file.
.RE
.RE
.sp
\fBhook\fP \fBinstall\fP | \fBuninstall\fP | \fBstatus\fP
.RS 4
Manage the \fBcommit\-msg\fP git hook. \fBinstall\fP creates the hook to run
\fBcz lint\fP on each commit. \fBuninstall\fP removes it. \fBstatus\fP shows whether
the hook is installed.
.RE
.SH "OPTIONS"
.sp
\fB\-c\fP, \fB\-\-config\-file\fP \fIFILE\fP
.RS 4
Use \fIFILE\fP instead of \fB.gitcommitizen\fP. Searches parent directories if
not specified.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-h\fP, \fB\-\-help\fP
.RS 4
Display usage information and exit.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-\-version\fP
.RS 4
Display version information and exit.
.RE
.SH "FILES"
.sp
\fB.gitcommitizen\fP
.RS 4
Project configuration file. See \fBgitcommitizen\fP(5) for format. If no
configuration is found, the Angular convention is used (feat, fix, docs,
style, refactor, perf, test, build, ci, chore, revert).
.RE
.SH "EXAMPLES"
.sp
Create and commit interactively
.RS 4
git commit \-m "$(cz)"
.RE
.sp
Lint the last commit message
.RS 4
git log \-1 \-\-pretty=%B | cz lint
.RE
.sp
Lint before committing (commit\-msg hook)
.RS 4
cz lint < "$1"
.RE
.sp
Lint silently (exit status only)
.RS 4
cz lint \-q < "$1" || exit 1
.RE
.sp
Show resolved configuration
.RS 4
cz parse
.RE
.sp
Generate a starter configuration
.RS 4
cz init
.RE
.sp
Install the commit\-msg hook
.RS 4
cz hook install
.RE
.SH "EXIT STATUS"
.sp
\fB0\fP
.RS 4
Success.
.RE
.sp
\fB1\fP
.RS 4
Runtime error (lint validation failed, missing dependency, config not found,
not a git repository).
.RE
.sp
\fB2\fP
.RS 4
Usage error (invalid arguments).
.RE
.sp
\fB130\fP
.RS 4
User cancelled (SIGINT).
.RE
.SH "DEPENDENCIES"
.sp
\fBgum\fP(1)
.RS 4
Required for interactive mode (\fBcreate\fP). Install from
.URL "https://github.com/charmbracelet/gum" "" ""
.RE
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.sp
\fBgit\-commit\fP(1), \fBgitcommitizen\fP(5), \fBgum\fP(1)
.sp
.URL "https://www.conventionalcommits.org" "Conventional Commits" ""
